This photo also appears in the <a href="http://memory.loc.gov/service/sgp/sgpnyt/1916/191602/19160213/0001.pdf" rel="nofollow">Picture Section</a> of <i>The New York Times</i> on February 13, 1916, with the following caption:<blockquote>”LOUIS W. HILL, SON OF JAMES J. HILL AND HEAD OF THE GREAT NORTHERN RAILWAY, REVIEWING THE ST. PAUL OUTDOOR SPORTS CARNIVAL PARADE FROM THE STEPS OF THE MINNESOTA STATE CAPITOL. (<i>Photo by  Bain News Service</i>)”</blockquote> — although clearly, Kilted Cowboy, you write a better caption than the <i>Times</i>!

&nbsp;
